  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/news/\" rel=\"tag\">科技新闻</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"cn.engadget.com/2014/03/25/chiropractors-claim-that-excessive-texting-lowers-your-life-span/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/adam/d11ed52bd784f02e455e827321746340/TEXTINGISBAD.jpg\" style=\"width: 620px; height: 394px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n长期低着头发短讯会对颈部有坏影响已是人所共知的吧，但美国脊医协会的研究则有一个更深层的发现。他们指出不只是低头族的颈会被影响，而且更会因为操作手机时的驼背的姿势而影响正常呼吸。在有关人士老来之时，便有可能会因而有心血管疾病（有机会间接缩短寿命）。他们研究的结论就是每个人都应该找他们本地的脊医来为他们检查一下脊椎。由脊医劝大家去看脊医可能会有点利益冲突，只是用电子装置（不管是否手机吧）时要有正确姿势则是人人应做的。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/03/25/chiropractors-claim-that-excessive-texting-lowers-your-life-span/\">Engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.united-chiropractic.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Mobile-Device-Use.pdf\">United Chiropractic Association（PDF）</a></div>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/26/chiropractors-claim-that-excessive-texting-lowers-your-life-span/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20856797/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/03/26/chiropractors-claim-that-excessive-texting-lowers-your-life-span/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
